  						  <table border='0' width='92%' cellspacing='0' cellpadding='5'>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' bgcolor='#0E024D' class='spti2' colspan='2'>CAZIC THULE</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
		<td align='left' class='db' vAlign='top'><img align=right src=''> Located within the heart of the Feerrott forest, the lost temple of the god Cazic Thule holds a race of the Cazic's own design, the Thulian Lizardmen. This temple, lost for ages, has recently been rediscovered by the Trolls and Ogres who have waged war upon these Lizardmen for as long as can be remembered. Also within the depths of the temple can be found the mortal incarnation of Cazic Thule himself, the <a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com/data/monsters.asp?Action=Description&Id=89'>Avatar of Fear</a>.

<p>Cazic Thule is a popular dungeon for the mid-level, 20 to mid-30's adventurer. As with most popular dungeons, the trains are viscious, but the spoils are rewarding. There are many sections of the temple, each one dropping popular mid-level loot. These sections include the maze, the archon temple, the throne room, the green room, and the avatar room.

<p>The maze is the lowest area of Cazic Thule. To access this area take the door to your immediate right after entering the main courtyard of the zone. This area is inhabited by the easiest of the lizardman, and is safe for a party of 20th level or higher adventurers. Within the maze are many safe areas, known as the "Dead Ends." At each dead end a party will usually setup and pull the denziens of the maze where they may safely fight without attracting the attention of other lizardmen. Within the maze are a few notable named monsters as well. Most common is The Radiant who drops radiant gloves, an item used in the enchanter <a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com/data/items.asp?Action=Description&Id=315'>Incandescent Gloves</a> quest. Also within the maze is the <a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com/data/monsters.asp?Action=Description&Id=3833'>Clay Golem</a>. The first of the three Thulian Golems, it drops the <a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com/data/items.asp?Action=Description&Id=581'>Lizardskin Tribal Mask</a> as his rare and Bits of Golem Clay as his common.

<p>At the upper 20s to low 30s, the Throne Room becomes possible. To reach the throne room, take the left most door from the courtyard and follow it straight to the end of the hall. There are normally two groups within the Throne Room, "TR Left" and "TR Right." The Throne Room can be a difficult area to control, but with the proper tactics you can gain much experience and some of the best mid-level items. There are three named monsters in this area. The first is the <b><a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com/data/monsters.asp?Action=Description&Id=2822'>Tae Ew Deviner</a></b>. The <b><a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com/data/monsters.asp?Action=Description&Id=2822'>Tae Ew Deviner</a></b> is an enchanter, so he will have a pet. Also, watch out for his charm! His most common drop is the <b><a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com/data/items.asp?Action=Description&Id=749'>Lizardscale Mantle</a></b>, a popular wisdom caster item. His rare drop is the <a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com/data/items.asp?Action=Description&Id=140'>Ravenscale Bracer</a>, a rogues best bracer until higher levels. Next to the Deviner spawns the Tae Ew Templar. The <a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com/data/monsters.asp?Action=Description&Id=2824'>Templar</a> is a cleric and can heal himself and other mobs. Dropped by him most often is the popular Lizardscale Cloak, an excellent melee and caster item. As his rare, the Templar will drop <a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com/data/items.asp?Action=Description&Id=551'>Ravenscale Legs</a>, another piece in the <a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com/data/items.asp?SearchString=ravenscale&Action=QuickSearch'>Ravenscale set</a>. Lastly the second Thulian Golem is found on the top floor of this throne room. The <a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com/data/monsters.asp?Action=Description&Id=3835'>Stone Golem</a> drops a Shard of Golem Stone as his cummon drop. Rarely he will drop the headpiece for the <a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com/data/items.asp?SearchString=ravenscale&Action=QuickSearch'>Ravenscale set</a>, the <a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com/data/items.asp?Action=Description&Id=476'>Ravenscale Coif</a>.

<p>Another popular area for 20s to low 30s is the Archon Temple, also known as Four Corners. To reach this one must traverse the maze to the very end, exiting through a door in the back. Outside this door is the temple. Along the four edges of the temple groups will setup and pull to each corner. The only rare spawn in this area is the <a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com/data/monsters.asp?Action=Description&Id=3235'>Tae Ew Archon</a>. The Archon drops the last piece in the Lizardscale series as his common drop, the <a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com/data/items.asp?Action=Description&Id=1973'>Lizardscale Belt</a>. His rare drop is yet another piece of Ravenscale, this time the <a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com/data/items.asp?Action=Description&Id=1207'>Ravenscale Arms</a>. Also spawning along the temple are Lizardman Crusaders who drop pieces of decaying armor used in the Shadowknight Darkforge Armor quests.

<p>The Green Room is a suitable place for a high 20s to mid 30s group to hunt. To access this room climb right above the zone hallway while in the courtyard, and follow the pool down. After reaching the Blue Pool keep going through the hallway to the Green Pool. At the Green Pool are many tough aligators. Also, the last Thulian Golem, the <a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com/data/monsters.asp?Action=Description&Id=2777'>Steel Golem</a>, spawns here. This Golem drops Bits of Golem Metal as his common loot and the <a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com/data/items.asp?Action=Description&Id=402'>Golem Metal Wand</a> as uncommon loot. As a rare drop he drops a Ravenscale piece, the <a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com/data/items.asp?Action=Description&Id=328'>Ravenscale Gloves</a>. 

<p>The last area of Cazic Thule is the Avatar room. There are three ways to access the Avatar room. The first way is through the Pyramid. To access the Pyramid go through the door that is straight at the end of the Courtyard and follow the hallway. Inside the Pyramid is a drop that will take you to the Avatar's bubble. You must swim through this bubble and drop down to the room below to reach the Avatar. Also, outside the Pyramid, can be found Silvered Guards. These guards drop the Silvered Wand, used in the Enchanter Rod of Insidious Glamour quest. The second way to reach the Avatar room is to proceed as if you were going to the Throne Room, however then taking the door that can be found immediatly to your right. This will lead you to the inside of the Pyramid, where you must once again drop down through the bubble. Lastly, you can avoid the Pyramid alltogether by swimming through the sewer grid at the far end of the entrance courtyard. When you first enter the sewers go straight for two rooms, go north one room, then take an immediate left. This will lead you directly to the Avatar's bubble. Within the bubble spawns the incarnation of Cazic Thule, the <a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com/data/monsters.asp?Action=Description&Id=89'>Avatar of Fear</a>. Most commonly dropped off the Avatar of Fear is the <a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com/data/items.asp?Action=Description&Id=819'>Bladed Thulian Claws</a>. As his rare drop the Avatar has the <a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com/data/items.asp?Action=Description&Id=191'>Ravenscale Chest</a>, completing the <a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com/data/items.asp?SearchString=ravenscale&Action=QuickSearch'>Ravenscale set</a>.

<p>As a low 20s to mid 30s dungeon, Cazic Thule is excellent. Popular items are abundant as well as very good experience. Because this is an outdoor zone, spells such as Spirit of Wolf will function. Invisibilty works fairly well around almost all the monsters except a few, such as the alligators. Because of Cazic Thule's popularity, trains are a common happening. Also Ogre bouncers are an ever present danger to a good race traveller heading to the dungeon, so stay on guard and avoid main paths.</td>
		<td width='18%' align='right' class='db' valign='top'><font class=dbti>Zone Information</font><br><a href='http://forums.castersrealm.com/cgi-bin/eq/forumdisplay.cgi?action=topics&forum=Cazic+Thule&number=190&DaysPrune=5&LastLogin='>Forum</a><br><a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com/data/zones.asp?Action=ListByMonsters&SubAction=ShowAll&ZoneId=15'>Monsters</a><br><a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com/data/zones.asp?Action=ListItems&SubAction=ShowAll&ZoneId=15'>Items</a><br> <a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com/data/maps.asp?Action=Description&Id=15'>Map</a>
    </tr>
